# While Loop - Print "Hello World" 10 Times

Here are a few examples in different programming languages:

## Python
```python
count = 0
while count < 10:
    print("Hello World")
    count += 1
```

## JavaScript
```javascript
let count = 0;
while (count < 10) {
    console.log("Hello World");
    count++;
}
```

## Java
```java
int count = 0;
while (count < 10) {
    System.out.println("Hello World");
    count++;
}
```

## C++
```cpp
int count = 0;
while (count < 10) {
    std::cout << "Hello World" << std::endl;
    count++;
}
```

## C#
```csharp
int count = 0;
while (count < 10) {
    Console.WriteLine("Hello World");
    count++;
}
```

All of these examples:
1. Initialize a counter variable to 0
2. Check if the counter is less than 10
3. Print "Hello World"
4. Increment the counter by 1
5. Repeat until the counter reaches 10

